reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Easy enough to put together as long as you look at the instructions, it's a mesh so I'm sure I could wash it if I had to or just hose it off. Holds about five men's shoes. Six lady shoes or children shoes. I also have two youth jackets hanging on it. Great for next to the kitchen door and has slim profile

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 3, 2023
reviews.reviewText: It fits where I want it. It’s narrow enough for my entry way. I’ll give it maybe 2-3 years of life, though, as the material seems to be flimsy; it does the job for now.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Awkward to Put Together without Help | Sturdy & Airy
reviews.reviewText: I had a time putting this together. Instructions are good though. Once assembled the unit is steady and holds about 2.5 pairs of shoes per shelf - so about 10 pairs of shoes in total for me.I really like the mesh shelving as they allow full air movements around the shoes top, sides and bottom.Materials are sturdy and color blends well into most any color scheme. However, I would have liked the screws to be black as well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Horrible instructions. website photo mis-leading.
reviews.reviewText: Pros: All parts were included. Liked the size.Cons: Instructions were very unclear, one step not even included. No picture of finished product to go by, difficult to assemble. I usually don't have an issue putting things together. I wanted a narrow shoe rack for entryway. This was a good size. The description said 'mesh' The website photo made it look like wire mesh. It is cloth mesh, quite flimsy. Will not work for me, I will be returning.
